  "texts": [
    "We conducted an extensive literature review to gather available soil organic carbon (SOC) measurements in the U.S. Midwest.",
    "This effort involved data from 18 sites, each with multiple SOC measurements at the plot level (~10 m) after 2000, facilitating ΔSOC validation for the KGML-ag-Carbon model (Fig. S16, Table S1).",
    "Observed data such as bulk density, initial SOC stock in the top 30 cm, and rotation management were integrated into the input feature when applicable.",
    "Other inputs were directly derived from our 250-m-resolution regional database, such as weather forcings and GPP based on the sites' geophysical locations.",
    "We have used an empirical equation 72 to simulate the percentage fraction of SOC at different depths to total stock (assumed to be SOC in 0-100 cm), expressed as:"
  ],
